fields.bio: Sara is the Agile Delivery Manager for 2 of BHP's 5 newly created Digital Factories whose aim is to deliver high-quality software at velocity to our customers in the mining operations. As part of her role, Sara leads the ways of working and improvements to how we operate as a department.

Melodie’s strength lies in combining technical proficiency with strong business acumen and evaluating strategic options for critical business decisions. Passionate about emerging technology and trends that have the capability to solve for complex business problems and create a meaningful impact.

Kelly’s career includes executive roles in some of Australia's biggest companies - Origin energy, Channel 9 and Telstra. She recently took on the role as Group Technology Officer at BHP to drive their digital transformation agenda. Kelly loves spending time with her family and time at the beach.

Melanie raised one of Australia’s largest early-stage investment rounds as CEO of Canva. Canva empowers millions to reach their goals, whether that's landing a job with a stylish resume, getting a business going with great marketing material or connecting through social media graphics.

Juliana Rotich pioneered new web tools for crowdsourcing crisis information. Originally from Kenya, she studied IT at university and became a blogger. Her software firm came to prominence during the Kenyan election crisis in 2007, using web, mobile and geolocation data to provide report updates.
When Nicola landed her job as Facebook’s vice president for Europe, the Middle East and Africa, she was labelled as a poster girl for working mothers...
